name: Mary McGrady
bio:
✝️ Believer in Jesus Christ
Special needs mama who's battling stage 4 rectal cancer

social_posts.post_text:
Waiting in admissions to go back for surgery. Ready to get this over with! Colon prep was really really rough. Like the worst cramps I've ever had in my life that lasted for 14 hours 😪 So ready to be done with this 
#colostomysurgery #colostomybag

Recovering well! So glad to have my mom here with me ❤ Surgery went really well. I'm comfortable for the most part, just sore. My bowels are awake and thats really important after getting a colostomy bag. So far so good!
So glad to be home 🏡 😌

This is the first post surgery pic I've taken. I kept meaning to take a pic right after surgery but never did. I wanted to be able to compare so I could visually note how the swelling has gone down. 
Still swollen, but significantly less so than last week.
There are 4 laproscopic incisions and then the area where my surgeon brought my colon out. 
Its crazy to me that this is my belly. I am so very thankful that I was able to get this colostomy bag. It has already made my life much better.

Felt good enough to take our family pic today! Woohoo!!!
The last 2 days I have been able to be in the living room laying on the couch instead of in bed. Big accomplishments and so happy to be with Garner more 🎉
 
The reason I've had a harder time getting out of bed is cause I had spent so long laying in bed prior to surgery. I've lost quite a bit of muscle, especially in my legs. So I'm celebrating the milestones!
Garner told Santa what he wants for Christmas 🎄 🎅🏻
My heart ❤

Merry Christmas everyone! 🎄🎅🏻❤
Our local fire department chose Garner as the child they gave gifts to this year. Back in May we had a scare with G and called them. They were so kind and compassionate. The reason they picked us is because they said our family stuck in their minds 🥰 
There is so much good in this world and so many amazing people.
Our happy, handsome, sweet boy ❤
Best present ever was spending the day with my family ❤ My heart is full and I am content

Back to chemo today. First time back since October. Can't say my chemo break was nice cause it wasn't. Too much pain and then surgery and then more pain. We are trying to get a handle on the pain to make me comfortable and its been hard. Hoping to catch a break soon.

My beautiful boys had a fun father son outing today. John Thomas has done an excellent job keeping Garner entertained during this very long Christmas break. We know G is ready to go back to school Monday and will be so excited to see his friends and teachers!

I'd like to ask for prayers for my Pop. On Friday morning he suffered a traumatic brain injury from a fall and an AVM (a cluster of blood vessels in his brain ruptured). He had emergency brain surgery but has not woken up since he fell Friday.
My Pop is the strongest man of faith I've ever known. This first picture here was taken just after he prayed for John Thomas and I during our wedding ceremony. 
Thank you in advance for praying 🙏 ❤

My grandad, Pop, gained his wings today 🥺 He was the greatest of men, strong in his faith, loved his family, and constant always.
My mom told me that he still had on his bracelet I gave him when I was diagnosed with cancer. It read "I wear this for my granddaughter". Other than his hospital gown it was the only other thing he had on. Mom said now he can go directly to Jesus and ask him to heal me. Oh my Pop i would much rather have you here but I know Jesus is rejoicing and welcoming you home.  Until we meet again at those pearly gates, Pop.

Happy 40th Birthday to my best friend! 
I hope you have a fun day celebrating 🎉💕
I love you so much John Thomas!

I feel like I have been struggling more and more as time goes on. Not just with pain but with energy, stamina, extreme  insomnia, weakness, being bed ridden, rapid heart rate all the time, constant fistula discharge that prevents good sleep, muscle loss, loss of appetite, weight loss, upset gut, feelings of wishing the Lord would just call me home and end the suffering if he isn't going to heal me. My cancer journey has been increasingly more painful and discouraging. Nothing seems to go right and there's never any good news. And ever since I caught that bug 2 weeks ago I have really been feeling awful. 
I'm being raw and vulnerable right now cause I'm tired of it all. Im so very tired of fighting a loosing battle. 
I need a miracle right now. I need a break from all this suffering. My faith is struggling cause I dont feel like the Lord will ever answer my prayers. Even just a small sign that he is listening would help. 
Ok I'm done venting. 
#stage4cancer #cancersucks

Today was a long day at the Ingram Cancer Center. First I spoke with my oncologist about my scan results. We knew there would be growth. What I wasn't expecting to hear is that the rectal tumor is pushing into the bladder. This had been causing me issues with peeing. There is growth in some of the lung tumors plus a new one. And also spots in my liver grew. My oncologist is hopeful that getting back to regular treatment will help, no more breaks! 
Got labs done and then saw my nurse practioner who showed me my hemoglobin and red blood cells are too low. Showing signs of anemia. C++id fatigue and chemo/cancer fatigue plus low red blood cells explains why walking to the bathroom feels like running a marathon. And my white blood cells are too high. Also seeing some fluid retention in my colon but I'm unclear on what that means.
 So I headed to the infusion center for a urinalysis and blood cultures to check for signs of infection. Then I got chemo and after chemo I got a blood transfusion. Hoping tomorrow they will let me know results from the urinalysis and blood cultures. 
I hate that there wasn't any really good news but I'm glad to have some answers to why I've been having these issues.
#colorectalcancer #stage4cancer #cancersucks

It has been the roughest week of my life. Way too many details to write out now.
I will say abscesses are excruciating, non stop fevers are exhausting, and cancer sucks.
Been in the hospital for 6 days now. Just had a sedated MRI of an abscess near my rectal tumor. Praying hard they can fix it.
Thats all I have energy to share right now.
#cancersucks #rectalcancer

So sick, still in the hospital with fever and mystery infection. They did a biopsy of the abscess and are waiting to see if any bacteria grows.
Not sure what the future holds for me. They're talking antibiotics for life to try get me back to chemo.
I love you all and appreciate all the love and support ❤
Even though they couldn't get rid of my infection and im still running fevers and on antibiotics it is really nice being home.

Quick update video (swipe right). Feeling very scared and overwhelmed with all these fast changes. Things are changing in a bad way  quicker than I anticipated and im not ready to not be here. Prayers please!!!

Devastated. I got moved to an inpatient hospice facility yesterday.

 My liver is riddled with tumors, the mystery infection hasn't cleared up. I cannot safely get treatment with an infection. 

Its not the way I imagined it going. And it happened much faster than we expected. 

I love you all and appreciate everything yall have done for my family and I. Please continue to pray for my family.
I cant explain how happy it made me to get outside today ☺

Our sweet, beautiful Mary went to be with her Lord on Thursday, April 6th at 7:20pm after a long and difficult battle with colorectal cancer. In her final hours, she was surrounded by her husband, parents, and siblings. Although we are all devastated, Mary was confident in her faith and we are rejoicing that she is whole and complete and no longer suffering. 
 
Mary was the most beautiful person inside and out and had a light inside of her that was present for all to see. She lived her life with joy, she loved freely and never had an unkind word to say, she was a fighter and protector, and gracious to all who cared for her. Mary impacted thousands of lives as she openly shared her story here on social media. Mary’s gift for lighting up every room that she entered remained constant throughout her journey with cancer. 
 
On behalf of all of us who love her, we cannot adequately express our gratitude to the hundreds of people who have been faithful prayer warriors throughout Mary’s journey with cancer. Your prayers were felt until the very end. In the last week of Mary’s life, she expressed that even in facing death, God still hadn’t given up on her.
 
We will celebrate Mary’s life in a funeral service on Saturday, April 15th at 1:00pm at Christ Presbyterian Church in Nashville, TN (2323 Old Hickory Blvd, Nashville, TN 37215). All are welcome to attend. Mary has asked that in lieu of flowers, donations be made to fund research for colorectal cancer.

✝️ Believer in Jesus Christ
Special needs mama who's battling stage 4 rectal cancer
